The newly constructed 4.3km Old Ota Road, Lagos Ogun Boundary Road in Agbado Oke-Odo Local Council Development Area to be inaugurated by Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu on Friday, February 19, 2021. The dualised road with median is complemented with a 260m long/wide bridge fitted with street lights and is expected to open up commercial activities within the axis and improve inter-connectivity along major road networks.        